Found in litter in rainforest in southern and central eastern 
<collectingRegion id="7940F84FC327731A90C4FD436575FD41" box="[1163,1295,691,717]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Queensland</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="23BF2A28C327731A9151FD43650AFD41" box="[1310,1392,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–19" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,777,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-282@7.[151,1436,777,1957]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 15–19. Papuaneon eungella n. sp. Male paratype (KS116472): 15 anterior view; palp: 16 posterior, 17 ventral, 18 anterior; 19 map showing known and predicted distributions. Scale: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6610170" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6610170/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
